'''''Under Southern Skies''''' is a 1984 video game published by [[The Avalon Hill Game Company]].

==Gameplay==
''Under Southern Skies'' is a game in which the player must contend with one German warship in the shipping lanes of the South Atlantic, in a strategic tactical naval wargame.<ref name="CGW16"/>

==Reception==
Johnny Wilson reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "USS has a few relatively minor problems [...] but it makes up for them in the graphic presentation."<ref name="CGW16">{{cite magazine |last=Wilson |first=Johnny |title=Micro-Reviews |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=June 1984 |volume=1 |issue=16 |pages=30}}</ref>

